{
  "article_id": "Engelhardt1923",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "In the latter part of the nineteenth century much was written and printed about "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said to have been rescued from one of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Santa Barbara Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". We have before us three different versions which agree on the main points, but vary in details. In brief, the story is to the effect that in 1835 "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " had the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " ("
      },
      {
        "text": "Worse is Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "), "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Charles Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sail over to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the farthest from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in order to bring "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The weather was stormy when "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", about twenty in number, were hurried into the boats, and all speed was made to reach "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In the excitement "
      },
      {
        "text": "a child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was left behind which "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "supposed had been carried aboard in the arms of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a sailor",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The frantic mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " implored "
      },
      {
        "text": "the men",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " to return. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The captain",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", however, replied that he must reach a place of safety, but that later they would go back for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Thereupon, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mother",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a widow of about twenty-five years of age, jumped overboard and struck out through the kelpy waters for ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "shore. In a moment she was lost in the seething waves. ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " with "
      },
      {
        "text": "the affrighted islanders",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " huddled together on deck staggered through the boiling waves and storm, and eventually reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Some of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " were sent to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", others went to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "ci_sg",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " wanted to return to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was in demand on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and so "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "her babe",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were forgotten."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Their uncertain fate lay heavy on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the kind-hearted Mission Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "; but it was not till 1850 that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Fr. González Rúbio",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " found a man, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Thomas Jeffries",
        "entity_key": "tje",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who for $200 agreed to visit "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and bring over "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He made the attempt, but found no living being on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In the following year, "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a convert to the Catholic Faith, accompanied by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jeffries",
        "entity_key": "tje",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and a crew of Indians, sailed over to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and remained there six weeks without discovering any trace of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In 1852 another unsuccessful trip was made. In July, 1853, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " made one more attempt in company with "
      },
      {
        "text": "Carl Ditman",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", alias "
      },
      {
        "text": "Charlie Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Irish cook",
        "entity_key": "col",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and "
      },
      {
        "text": "a crew of Mission Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". This time "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was discovered, and willingly came along to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever had his family",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "sni",
          "ini",
          "gnijr",
          "jacobni",
          "mrni",
          "mrfni"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " care for her in his own house. Whatever her language, no one could be found along "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " who understood her, nor could she make out what was said to her in Spanish or in any of the dialects spoken among the shore Indians. "
      },
      {
        "text": "So she managed to make herself understood by means of signs.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " When discovered she wore a gown made of bird skins and feathers. "
      },
      {
        "text": "On shore she enjoyed her new life, and displayed no symptoms of ferocity.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She would go around to different homes and dance Indian dances, ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " relates. Clothes were her especial delight.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Unfortunately, change of diet cut short the life of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "; for under that name she was conditionally baptized by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Sanchez",
        "entity_key": "sanchez",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", according to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She would doubtless have lived many years, had some caution been exercised with regard to her food; but she was supplied to her heart's content with dainty foods, from which she gradually sickened and died. It was also claimed that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " after her death found her resting-place in the cemetery of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Such is the story in brief of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Lone Woman of San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Were it not that Mr. Nidever's fame for veracity appears above suspicion, we should declare the whole story a myth, for the reason that, after a close examination of the Baptismal Registers at "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and at "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Parish Church of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "sbparishchurch",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", we failed to discover any entry recording the woman's Baptism in either "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " or "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Parish Church",
        "entity_key": "sbparishchurch",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Likewise, there is no record noted of her burial in the Mission Cemetery."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"That the story is literally true,\" writes "
      },
      {
        "text": "Stephen Bowers",
        "entity_key": "sbo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " in the Ventura Observer, December 20, 1892, \"there can be no doubt whatever. We received it from Captain Nidever's own lips several years before his death. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The writer",
        "entity_key": "sbo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was personally acquainted with him from 1874 until his death which occurred about 1886. He was much respected in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where he lived more than fifty years. We never heard his integrity called in question by anyone. . . . The account may also be found in the archives of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", preserved by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission Fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". We secured a translation of their record of the event by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a competent Spanish scholar",
        "entity_key": "spanscholar",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "fifteen years ago.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Bancroft",
        "entity_key": "hba",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " corroborates what "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Bowers",
        "entity_key": "sbo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " says of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "; but the last statement regarding the presence in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission Archives",
        "entity_key": "sbmarchive",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " of a paper or document containing the story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Lone Woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " we cannot verify. We found no such account among the numerous papers in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission Archives",
        "entity_key": "sbmarchive",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " nor anywhere else."
      }
    ]
  ]
}